== Events == * [[:en:Jōgen (Kamakura period)|Shōgen]] 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1207|ja|1207|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1207|qq=}} [[:en:November 16|November 16]] ） – The era was changed from [[:en:Ken'ei|Ken'ei]] to [[:en:Jōgen (Kamakura period)|Shōgen]] . * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 14th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1637|ja|1637|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1637|qq=}} [[:en:December 11|December 11]] ） – The Shimabara Rebellion: Farmers from Amakusa and Shimabara rose against oppressive daimyō and anti-Christian policies. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 5th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1858|ja|1858|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1858|qq=}} [[:en:November 30|November 30]] ） – [[:en:Tokugawa Iemochi|Tokugawa Iemochi]] ascended as the 14th shōgun. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1868|ja|1868|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1868|qq=}} [[:en:December 8|December 8]] ） – Enomoto Takeaki and others occupied the five-pointed star fortress, [[:en:Goryōkaku|Goryōkaku]] , in Hakodate.
