{{Not to be confused with|October 25|qq=October 25}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月廿五|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 25일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 25''' is the 25th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}} .
== Events == * [[:en:Jōgen (Kamakura period)|Shōgen]] 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1207|1207]] [[:en:November 16|November 16]] ） – The era was changed from [[:en:Ken'ei|Ken'ei]] to [[:en:Jōgen (Kamakura period)|Shōgen]] . * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 14th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1637|1637]] [[:en:December 11|December 11]] ） – The Shimabara Rebellion: Farmers from Amakusa and Shimabara rose against oppressive daimyō and anti-Christian policies. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 5th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1858|1858]] [[:en:November 30|November 30]] ） – [[:en:Tokugawa Iemochi|Tokugawa Iemochi]] ascended as the 14th shōgun. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:December 8|December 8]] ） – Enomoto Takeaki and others occupied the five-pointed star fortress, [[:en:Goryōkaku|Goryōkaku]] , in Hakodate.
== Births == * {{ill|Manrei|ja|万暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Manrei|qq=}} 20th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1592|1592]] [[:en:November 28|November 28]] ） – [[:en:Hong Taiji|Hontai-ji]] (皇太極), the 2nd emperor of the Qing († [[:en:1643|1643]] ). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:December 8|December 8]] ） – {{ill|Tokutomi Roka|ja|徳富蘆花|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokutomi Roka|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 徳冨蘆花}} , a novelist († [[:en:1927|1927]] ).
